        <section class="about-section about-reveal">
            <h3>What I'm Exploring</h3>
            <p class="about-lead">My biggest interest right now is the <strong>combination of AI and enterprise software</strong>. In particular, I keep exploring these questions.</p>
            <div class="about-explore">
                <div class="explore-block">
                    <h4>AI &times; ERP</h4>
                    <p>Beyond just reading ERP data, can AI&hellip;</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>understand the state of the business,</li>
                        <li>interpret business rules,</li>
                        <li>detect anomalies,</li>
                        <li>and suggest or take action at the right moment?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="explore-block">
                    <h4>AI &times; Software Development</h4>
                    <p>Beyond generating code, can AI&hellip;</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>understand the existing architecture,</li>
                        <li>trace business rules,</li>
                        <li>analyze the impact of changes,</li>
                        <li>perform code reviews,</li>
                        <li>and accumulate development experience as organizational knowledge?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="explore-block">
                    <h4>AI &times; Knowledge</h4>
                    <p>Every project accumulates&hellip;</p>
                    <ul class="explore-inline">
                        <li>Architecture</li>
                        <li>Business Rule</li>
                        <li>Database Semantics</li>
                        <li>API</li>
                        <li>Decision</li>
                        <li>Work Log</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>&mdash; can these become a knowledge system that is <strong>continuously generated, connected, and updated</strong>, instead of depending on human memory?</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="about-lead">These questions are where my focus is today.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section about-reveal">
            <h3>How I Work</h3>
            <p class="about-lead">These are the principles I value.</p>
            <div class="about-cards about-principles">
                <div class="about-card">
                    <span class="principle-num">01</span>
                    <h4>Structure Before Complexity</h4>
                    <p>The more complex the problem, the less I rush to implement. I first find the structure, split responsibilities, and define boundaries.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="about-card">
                    <span class="principle-num">02</span>
                    <h4>Knowledge Should Survive People</h4>
                    <p>Knowledge must remain even when people move on. Code, documents, issues, decisions, and incident experience should become <strong>organizational assets</strong>, not personal memories.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="about-card">
                    <span class="principle-num">03</span>
                    <h4>Automate Repetition</h4>
                    <p>I automate whatever people repeat. AI should not add new work for people &mdash; it should <strong>naturally generate knowledge and raise productivity within existing workflows</strong>.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="about-card">
                    <span class="principle-num">04</span>
                    <h4>Build for the Future</h4>
                    <p>I prefer structures that can absorb the next change over implementations that only solve today's requirements &mdash; while <strong>investing in structure only where real extensibility is likely</strong>, rather than over-abstracting.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section about-reveal">
            <h3>Why This Wiki Exists</h3>
            <p class="about-lead">This wiki is not just a document store. It is a <strong>knowledge base</strong> where I accumulate what I learn while building, thinking, and experimenting &mdash; so it stays useful over time.</p>
            <div class="about-chips">
                <span class="about-chip">AI</span>
